          <p class="mb-4">Whether you're using MoodMeter as a quiet, private <strong>mood journal</strong> for your own <strong>mental health journal</strong> practice, or as a way to feel connected to others navigating similar ups and downs, the goal is the same: make checking in with yourself a small, sustainable daily habit. MoodMeter is a wellbeing tool, not a substitute for professional medical or mental health advice — but as a companion for everyday self-awareness, it's designed to be honest, low-pressure, and genuinely useful.</p>
